  { q: "Can I Airbnb my property in Markham?", a: "Not for stays under 30 days. Markham generally does not permit short-term rentals under 30 consecutive days unless very strict criteria are met. This is not a grey area or a lack of regulation. The city has actively restricted STRs. Rentals of 30 days or longer (mid-term rentals) are permitted and not subject to STR restrictions." },
  { q: "Why does Markham not allow short-term rentals?", a: "Markham has taken a housing-first approach, prioritizing long-term housing supply over tourism accommodation. With the city's rapid population growth and tight rental market, council decided that preserving residential units for permanent residents was more important than allowing Airbnb-style rentals. This aligns with the approach taken by nearby Halton Hills and Scugog, which also prohibit STRs." },
  { q: "What is the mid-term rental alternative in Markham?", a: "Rentals of 30 days or longer are not classified as short-term rentals and are not subject to the STR prohibition. Many Markham property owners earn strong income through furnished monthly rentals targeting corporate relocations, contract workers at local tech companies, families between homes, and newcomers settling in Canada. Markham's tech sector and diverse community create consistent demand for 1 to 6 month stays." },
  { q: "Can I Airbnb an investment property in Markham?", a: "No. Since STRs under 30 days are generally not permitted in Markham regardless of property type, this applies to both your primary home and any investment properties. For investment properties, mid-term rentals (30+ days) or traditional long-term leases are your options. Neighbouring Richmond Hill allows investment property Airbnbs with no restrictions." },
  { q: "Which cities near Markham allow Airbnb?", a: "Richmond Hill (immediately west) has no STR regulations at all, meaning no license, no night limit, no principal residence requirement, and no MAT. Ajax (south in Durham Region) is also unregulated. Pickering has no STR bylaws either. If you own property in any of these cities, you can operate a short-term rental without municipal restrictions." },
  { q: "Do Markham condo rules affect rentals?", a: "Yes. Even for mid-term rentals (30+ days), your condo corporation's declaration and rules may impose minimum lease terms (often 6 or 12 months), restrict furnished rentals, or require board approval for tenants. Always check your condo's governing documents before listing any rental, whether short-term or mid-term." },
  { q: "Do I need to collect HST on mid-term rentals in Markham?", a: "Rentals of 30 days or longer are generally exempt from HST if the tenant uses the unit as their primary place of residence during the stay. However, if you provide hotel-like services (daily housekeeping, meals, etc.) or the rental is under 30 days, HST applies. If your total taxable accommodation revenue exceeds $30,000 per year, you must register for HST." },
  { q: "Will Markham ever allow short-term rentals?", a: "It is possible but unlikely in the near future. Markham has not signaled any intention to reverse its position on STRs. The city continues to prioritize housing supply and affordability. If the political environment changes or if Ontario introduces provincial STR legislation that overrides municipal bans, the situation could shift. For now, plan around mid-term rentals as your primary strategy." }
];

