        <article class="article-content">
          <div class="article-intro">
            <p class="lead">If you're reading this, you probably own property in Markham and want to know if you can list it on Airbnb. The short answer: no, not for stays under 30 days.</p>
            <p class="lead">But that's not the end of the story. Markham's restriction on short-term rentals actually opens the door to a different (and often more profitable) strategy: furnished mid-term rentals. With IBM, AMD, Qualcomm, and dozens of tech companies in the area, there's serious demand for 30 to 90 day stays. Let's break down what the rules actually say, what your alternatives are, and where nearby you <em>can</em> Airbnb if you want to.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="short-answer">The Short Answer</h2>
          <p>Here's the quick summary for Markham property owners:</p>

          <div class="comparison-table">
            <div class="comparison-header">
              <div class="comparison-col">Question</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight">Markham (2026)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Can I Airbnb for stays under 30 days?</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>Generally no</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Are mid-term rentals (30+ days) allowed?</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>Yes</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">STR license available?</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>No (STRs not permitted)</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Municipal Accommodation Tax?</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>N/A</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Investment property STRs?</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>Not permitted</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Principal residence STRs?</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>Not permitted</strong></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>This is different from cities that simply haven't gotten around to regulating STRs yet. Markham has looked at the situation and decided: no. Whether you own your home or an investment condo, Airbnb stays under 30 days are off the table.</p>

          <h2 id="what-rules-say">What the Rules Actually Say</h2>
          <p>Markham's zoning bylaws do not permit short-term rental accommodations (stays under 30 consecutive days) in residential zones. Unlike cities such as Toronto, Mississauga, or Vaughan, which created licensing frameworks to allow STRs under certain conditions, Markham chose not to create any pathway for legal short-term rental operations.</p>

          <p>What this means in practice:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>No license to apply for.</strong> You can't get a permit because there is no permit category for STRs.</li>
            <li><strong>No registration system.</strong> There's no municipal registry for short-term rental operators.</li>
            <li><strong>Zoning enforcement.</strong> If a complaint is filed, the city can enforce the zoning bylaw and require you to stop operating.</li>
            <li><strong>Platforms may still list you.</strong> Airbnb doesn't automatically block listings in Markham, but operating would put you at risk of municipal enforcement.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h4>Operating Without Permission Is Risky</h4>
            <p>Some Markham hosts list properties on Airbnb despite the restriction. If a neighbour complains or the city runs an audit, you could face fines, forced removal of your listing, and potential legal action. The risk is real, and it's not worth it when mid-term rentals offer a legal and often more profitable alternative.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="why-restricted">Why Markham Restricts Short-Term Rentals</h2>
          <p>Markham's decision wasn't random. The city has been one of the fastest-growing municipalities in Canada, and the rental housing market is extremely tight. Here's the reasoning:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Housing supply.</strong> Markham's population has grown significantly over the past decade. Every unit converted from long-term rental to Airbnb is one less home available for residents. Council has prioritized keeping housing stock for people who actually live and work in the city.</li>
            <li><strong>Neighbourhood character.</strong> The city's established neighbourhoods (Unionville, Markham Village, Cornell) are predominantly residential. Rotating short-term guests can change the feel of a quiet street, and council heard that feedback from residents.</li>
            <li><strong>Enforcement simplicity.</strong> Rather than building a licensing and enforcement framework (which costs staff and money), Markham took the simpler approach: just don't allow it. No need for inspectors, registries, or compliance monitoring.</li>
          </ul>

          <p>You can agree or disagree with the reasoning. But for now, it's the reality on the ground.</p>

          <h2 id="mid-term-alternative">The Mid-Term Rental Alternative</h2>
          <p>Here's the good news: rentals of 30 days or longer are not classified as short-term rentals and are not subject to Markham's STR restriction. This is where the real opportunity lives.</p>

          <p>A furnished mid-term rental in Markham can earn significantly more than a traditional 12 month lease. Think about it this way:</p>

          <div class="comparison-table">
            <div class="comparison-header">
              <div class="comparison-col">Rental Type</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight">Typical Monthly Revenue</div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Long-term lease (unfurnished)</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>$2,200 to $2,800/mo</strong> (2-bed condo)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col highlight-green">Mid-term furnished rental</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>$3,500 to $5,000/mo</strong> (2-bed condo)</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>That's a 40% to 80% premium for furnishing your unit and renting to monthly guests instead of annual tenants. And because your tenants stay 30 to 90 days (sometimes longer), you're not dealing with the daily turnover, cleaning, and guest management that comes with nightly Airbnb.</p>

          <h3>Who Rents Mid-Term in Markham?</h3>
          <p>Markham has a uniquely strong tenant pool for mid-term rentals:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Tech workers on contract.</strong> IBM Canada's head office is in Markham. AMD, Qualcomm, Huawei, Lenovo, and dozens of other tech companies bring in contract workers for 3 to 6 month projects. These folks need furnished housing close to the office.</li>
            <li><strong>Corporate relocations.</strong> Families transferring to the GTA often land in Markham first, especially those with connections to the Chinese, South Asian, or Korean communities. They need a furnished place for 1 to 3 months while they search for a permanent home.</li>
            <li><strong>New immigrants.</strong> Markham is one of the most popular landing spots for newcomers to Canada. Furnished monthly rentals give families a stable base while they get settled, find jobs, and explore neighbourhoods.</li>
            <li><strong>Medical patients and families.</strong> Markham Stouffville Hospital and proximity to Sunnybrook create demand from patients and their families who need nearby accommodation for treatment periods.</li>
            <li><strong>Insurance displacement.</strong> When a Markham home has fire, flood, or other damage, the insurance company pays for temporary housing. These placements typically run 2 to 6 months and are very reliable payers.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="callout">
            <div class="callout-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
