            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">Income tax</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>All rental income</strong> must be reported to CRA</div>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-row">
              <div class="comparison-col">MAT</div>
              <div class="comparison-col highlight"><strong>N/A</strong> (Markham has no MAT and mid-term is exempt anyway)</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>Important details:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>HST exemption for residential rentals:</strong> If your tenant stays 30+ days and uses the unit as their residence (not a vacation), HST does not apply. This is a big advantage over short-term rentals, where HST kicks in at $30K/year revenue.</li>
            <li><strong>Income tax deductions:</strong> You can deduct mortgage interest, property tax, condo fees, insurance, furnishing costs (depreciated), cleaning between tenants, platform fees, and property management fees against your rental income.</li>
            <li><strong>CRA 2024 rule:</strong> The federal government now denies deductions on non-compliant STRs. Since you're operating a legal mid-term rental, this rule doesn't affect you. Another reason to stay on the right side of the rules.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="tips">Tips for Markham Property Owners</h2>

          <ul class="tips-list">
            <li><span class="tip-icon">1</span> <strong>Furnish your unit properly.</strong> Mid-term tenants expect a fully equipped home: bed linens, kitchenware, WiFi, a desk for remote work, and laundry access. Think "move in with a suitcase." The better your furnishing, the higher your nightly rate.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">2</span> <strong>List on Airbnb with a 30-night minimum.</strong> This is legal in Markham. Airbnb's platform gives you access to a massive pool of monthly renters. Combine it with Furnished Finder and direct outreach to local companies for maximum occupancy.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">3</span> <strong>Target corporate accounts.</strong> Reach out directly to IBM, AMD, and other Markham tech companies' HR and relocation departments. Many have budgets for temporary housing and prefer working with reliable local providers.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">4</span> <strong>Get proper insurance.</strong> Standard homeowner's insurance may not cover furnished rental activity, even for mid-term stays. Talk to your insurer about a landlord policy that covers furnished rentals. $2M liability coverage is the industry standard.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">5</span> <strong>Check your condo rules.</strong> Condo declarations may impose minimum lease terms, restrict furnished rentals, or require board approval. Read your declaration carefully. Some Markham condos require 6 or 12 month minimum leases, which would rule out mid-term stays.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">6</span> <strong>Price competitively.</strong> Mid-term rates in Markham for a furnished 2 bedroom condo typically run $3,500 to $5,000/month. Research comparable listings on Airbnb (filter for monthly stays) and Furnished Finder to set your price.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">7</span> <strong>Screen tenants carefully.</strong> Mid-term guests stay longer than Airbnb overnighters, so compatibility matters more. Verify employment, ask about the purpose of their stay, and trust your instincts. A bad 90 day tenant is much worse than a bad 2 night guest.</li>
            <li><span class="tip-icon">8</span> <strong>Consider professional management.</strong> If managing a furnished rental sounds like too much work, <a href="/services/mid-term-rental-management">mid-term rental management</a> companies (like us) handle everything from tenant screening to cleaning coordination. You collect monthly income without the daily operations.</li>
          </ul>

